  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Device</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>prothesis voice</intervention_name>
    <description>The device may be used for patient using another type of voice prosthesis, of for patient undergoing total laryngectomy. This device is definitively placed in two parts:The first one is introduced in the puncture (TEP) through the esophagus (retrograde way). The second part is then clipped on the first one through the tracheotomy orifice (anterograde way).A third part containing the valve can then be clipped in the prosthesis and easily removed in order to change it as often as necessary.</description>
  </intervention>
